In the [JIRA Supported Platforms documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA062/Supported+Platforms], its stated that we support specifically *Tomcat 7.0.29*. 

For the JIRA WAR installation process, if you use Tomcat 7.0.29 with any JIRA war distribution, the application context is exploded in the *work* directory of the Tomcat installation, e.g.:
{quote}
{{...\apache-tomcat-7.0.29\work\Catalina\localhost\jira}}
{quote}

The issue here is that the [War Installation documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Installing+JIRA+on+Tomcat+6.0+or+7.0] explicitly refers to Tomcat versions where the application context is exploded in the *webapps* directory:
{quote}
{{...\apache-tomcat-7.0.53\webapps\jira}}
{quote}
For Tomcat 7.0.29, there is no *jira* folder existing inside the webapps directory.

This creates some confusion, because in the case where you need to get Tomcat to *re-expand the WAR*, you need to delete the *expanded JIRA folder*, which in the documentation states that its in the *webapps* folder. for JIRA 7.0.29 this is not the case. We should either:
# Change the docs to reflect behaviour of Tomcat 7.0.29, OR
# Describe differences of both tomcat version behaviour inside the docs.

